# Pre-Researcher — ai-chatbot-for-customer-support

## Critical Research Items (Plan Gate: 2 blockers)

---

### 1. WebLLM CDN URL + Llama-3.2-1B Model ID — CONFIRMED

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| ESM CDN (unpinned) | `import * as webllm from "https://esm.run/@mlc-ai/web-llm"` |
| ESM CDN (pinned, safer) | `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mlc-ai/web-llm@0.2.84/+esm` |
| Latest version | `0.2.84` (also 0.2.83 on GitHub — both stable as of June 2026) |
| Model ID | `Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` |
| VRAM required | 879 MB (q4f16_1); 1129 MB (q4f32_1 — skip this one) |
| Model source | `https://huggingface.co/mlc-ai/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` |
| Context window | 4096 tokens |

**Usage:**
```js
import { CreateMLCEngine } from "https://esm.run/@mlc-ai/web-llm";
const engine = await CreateMLCEngine("Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC", {
  initProgressCallback: (p) => updateLoadingUI(p)
});
```

Models are downloaded on first use and cached in IndexedDB (~600-900 MB one-time download). Subsequent loads are instant from cache.

---

### 2. Transformers.js WASM Fallback — CONFIRMED + CRITICAL PACKAGE NAME CHANGE

**BLOCKER FOR PLAN:** The plan references `@xenova/transformers`. This is stale. The package was renamed starting v3.

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| **Correct package** | `@huggingface/transformers` (not `@xenova/transformers`) |
| `@xenova/transformers` status | Frozen at v2.17.2; no new updates; still works but EOL trajectory |
| Latest `@huggingface/transformers` | v4.2.0 |
| ESM CDN (unpinned) | `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers` |
| ESM CDN (pinned) | `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers@4.2.0/+esm` |
| Instruction model | `onnx-community/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct` |
| Instruction model dtype for WASM | `{ dtype: "q4", device: "wasm" }` |
| Embedding model (cosine sim) | `Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (Xenova-namespaced models still work in the new package) |
| Alt embedding (smaller, faster) | `mixedbread-ai/mxbai-embed-xsmall-v1` |

**WASM inference usage:**
```js
import { pipeline } from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers@4.2.0/+esm";
// Instruction (chat):
const chat = await pipeline("text-generation", "onnx-community/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct",
  { dtype: "q4", device: "wasm" });
// Embeddings (RAG cosine similarity):
const embed = await pipeline("feature-extraction", "Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2",
  { dtype: "fp32", device: "wasm" });
```

---

### 3. Deploy-Test (Playwright) — WASM Path Is The Only Tested Path

Playwright headless Chromium has NO WebGPU. This means:
- WebLLM (WebGPU path) will silently fail / skip in deploy-test
- The Transformers.js WASM path is **the primary path exercised by CI/deploy-test**
- Builder must treat WASM path as the real path, not a skeleton fallback
- Recommend: detect WebGPU support at runtime (`navigator.gpu`), fall to WASM immediately if absent; WASM path must produce real coherent answers, not just "I don't know"

---

## Nice-to-Have Items (non-critical, fidelity)

### 4. Zendesk Chat Widget UI Patterns

Standard Zendesk/Intercom widget anatomy for the builder to reference:
- **Launcher:** fixed bottom-right circle button (56x56px), brand color, chat bubble icon; badge for unread count
- **Panel:** 380px wide x 520px tall card (responsive), positioned above launcher with 16px gap; `box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.18)`
- **Header:** avatar/bot icon left, name + status dot ("Online"), minimize/close icons right; brand color background
- **Message feed:** scrollable; user bubbles right-aligned (brand accent), bot bubbles left-aligned (light gray); timestamps below each group
- **Input area:** textarea + send button; attach/emoji icons optional; "Powered by [agent name]" footer
- **Typing indicator:** three-dot pulse animation in bot bubble
- **Escalation card:** distinct yellow/orange card inside feed, agent avatar placeholder, "Connecting you to a human..." state
- **Zendesk ticket created card:** green checkmark icon, "Ticket #XXXX created", expected response time

